  "summary": "The text discusses the themes of divine retribution and prophecy, primarily focused on the aftermath of the crucifixion of Jesus Christ. It reflects on the biblical passage regarding the division of garments and casting lots, and interprets the turmoil among the mountains metaphorically as the severe consequences faced by the Jewish people after rejecting the Gospel. The historical context relates to the destruction and upheaval experienced by the Jews under the Roman emperors Vespasian and Hadrian. It is noted that the reason for God's wrath is not idolatry or other sins, but the rejection and blasphemy against the Gospel message.",
  "keywords": ["Anti-Judaism", "Emperor Hadrian", "Vengeance"]
